    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe type annotations for `vim.lsp.rpc.Dispatchers` in `runtime/lua/vim/lsp/rpc.lua` are inconsistent with their actual implementation in `runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua`.\n\n**Current (incorrect) type declarations in rpc.lua:**\n\n```lua\n--- @class vim.lsp.rpc.Dispatchers\n--- @field notification fun(method: vim.lsp.protocol.Method.ClientToServer.Notification, params: table)\n--- @field server_request fun(method: vim.lsp.protocol.Method.ClientToServer.Request, params: table): any?, lsp.ResponseError?\n```\n\n**Actual implementation in client.lua proves these should be `ServerToClient`:**\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/7a27c5b0c88097e65d2ac677ec17b075271b689f/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua#L466-L480\n\n1. `_notification` handler (line 1284):\n```lua\n--- @param method vim.lsp.protocol.Method.ServerToClient.Notification LSP method name\nfunction Client:_notification(method, params)\n```\n\n2. `_server_request` handler (line 1298):\n```lua\n--- @param method (vim.lsp.protocol.Method.ServerToClient) LSP method name\nfunction Client:_server_request(method, params)\n```\n\n**The mismatch:**\n- `Dispatchers.notification` is typed as `ClientToServer.Notification` but actually receives `ServerToClient.Notification`\n- `Dispatchers.server_request` is typed as `ClientToServer.Request` but actually receives `ServerToClient.Request`\n\nI may have misunderstood the intended design, and I'd appreciate any clarification. Thank you.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.1",
